  "doc_id": "776",
  "text": "E1A-transformed human embryonic kidney 293 (HEK 293E) cells were maintained in DMEM supplemented with 10% heat-inactivated fetal bovine serum (FBS). Transfection was by calcium phosphate precipitation; the total amount of DNA per transfected 60 mm dish was 3-5 µg. FL5.12 cells stably expressing Bcl-x L together with either wild-type or mutant Bad (FL5.12-Bcl-x L -Bad cells; a gift of S. Korsmeyer) were cultured as described [CITATION_1] except that recombinant IL-3 (0.5 ng ml -1 ) was used instead of WEHI-cell-conditioned media.",
